18X509_LOOKUP *X509_LOOKUP_new(X509_LOOKUP_METHOD *method)
19{
20 X509_LOOKUP *ret = OPENSSL_zalloc(sizeof(*ret));
21
22 if (ret == NULL) {
23 X509err(X509_F_X509_LOOKUP_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
24 return NULL;
25 }
26
27 ret->method = method;
28 if (method->new_item != NULL && method->new_item(ret) == 0) {
29 OPENSSL_free(ret);
30 return NULL;
31 }
32 return ret;
33}
34
35void X509_LOOKUP_free(X509_LOOKUP *ctx)
36{
37 if (ctx == NULL)
38 return;
39 if ((ctx->method != NULL) && (ctx->method->free != NULL))
40 (*ctx->method->free) (ctx);
41 OPENSSL_free(ctx);
42}

138static int x509_object_cmp(const X509_OBJECT *const *a,
139 const X509_OBJECT *const *b)
140{
141 int ret;
142
143 ret = ((*a)->type - (*b)->type);
144 if (ret)
145 return ret;
146 switch ((*a)->type) {
147 case X509_LU_X509:
148 ret = X509_subject_name_cmp((*a)->data.x509, (*b)->data.x509);
149 break;
150 case X509_LU_CRL:
151 ret = X509_CRL_cmp((*a)->data.crl, (*b)->data.crl);
152 break;
153 case X509_LU_NONE:
154 /* abort(); */
155 return 0;
156 }
157 return ret;
158}
159
160X509_STORE *X509_STORE_new(void)
161{
162 X509_STORE *ret = OPENSSL_zalloc(sizeof(*ret));
163
164 if (ret == NULL) {
165 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
166 return NULL;
167 }
168 if ((ret->objs = sk_X509_OBJECT_new(x509_object_cmp)) == NULL) {
169 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
170 goto err;
171 }
172 ret->cache = 1;
173 if ((ret->get_cert_methods = sk_X509_LOOKUP_new_null()) == NULL) {
174 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
175 goto err;
176 }
177
178 if ((ret->param = X509_VERIFY_PARAM_new()) == NULL) {
179 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
180 goto err;
181 }
182 if (!CRYPTO_new_ex_data(CRYPTO_EX_INDEX_X509_STORE, ret, &ret->ex_data)) {
183 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
184 goto err;
185 }
186
187 ret->lock = CRYPTO_THREAD_lock_new();
188 if (ret->lock == NULL) {
189 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_NEW, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
190 goto err;
191 }
192
193 ret->references = 1;
194 return ret;
195
196err:
197 X509_VERIFY_PARAM_free(ret->param);
198 sk_X509_OBJECT_free(ret->objs);
199 sk_X509_LOOKUP_free(ret->get_cert_methods);
200 OPENSSL_free(ret);
201 return NULL;
202}
203
204void X509_STORE_free(X509_STORE *vfy)
205{
206 int i;
207 STACK_OF(X509_LOOKUP) *sk;
208 X509_LOOKUP *lu;
209
210 if (vfy == NULL)
211 return;
212 CRYPTO_DOWN_REF(&vfy->references, &i, vfy->lock);
213 REF_PRINT_COUNT("X509_STORE", vfy);
214 if (i > 0)
215 return;
216 REF_ASSERT_ISNT(i < 0);
217
218 sk = vfy->get_cert_methods;
219 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_LOOKUP_num(sk); i++) {
220 lu = sk_X509_LOOKUP_value(sk, i);
221 X509_LOOKUP_shutdown(lu);
222 X509_LOOKUP_free(lu);
223 }
224 sk_X509_LOOKUP_free(sk);
225 sk_X509_OBJECT_pop_free(vfy->objs, X509_OBJECT_free);
226
227 CRYPTO_free_ex_data(CRYPTO_EX_INDEX_X509_STORE, vfy, &vfy->ex_data);
228 X509_VERIFY_PARAM_free(vfy->param);
229 CRYPTO_THREAD_lock_free(vfy->lock);
230 OPENSSL_free(vfy);
231}
232
233int X509_STORE_up_ref(X509_STORE *vfy)
234{
235 int i;
236
237 if (CRYPTO_UP_REF(&vfy->references, &i, vfy->lock) <= 0)
238 return 0;
239
240 REF_PRINT_COUNT("X509_STORE", a);
241 REF_ASSERT_ISNT(i < 2);
242 return ((i > 1) ? 1 : 0);
243}

245X509_LOOKUP *X509_STORE_add_lookup(X509_STORE *v, X509_LOOKUP_METHOD *m)
246{
247 int i;
248 STACK_OF(X509_LOOKUP) *sk;
249 X509_LOOKUP *lu;
250
251 sk = v->get_cert_methods;
252 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_LOOKUP_num(sk); i++) {
253 lu = sk_X509_LOOKUP_value(sk, i);
254 if (m == lu->method) {
255 return lu;
256 }
257 }
258 /* a new one */
259 lu = X509_LOOKUP_new(m);
260 if (lu == NULL) {
261 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_ADD_LOOKUP, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
262 return NULL;
263 }
264
265 lu->store_ctx = v;
266 if (sk_X509_LOOKUP_push(v->get_cert_methods, lu))
267 return lu;
268 /* malloc failed */
269 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_ADD_LOOKUP, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
270 X509_LOOKUP_free(lu);
271 return NULL;
272}

274X509_OBJECT *X509_STORE_CTX_get_obj_by_subject(X509_STORE_CTX *vs,
275 X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
276 X509_NAME *name)
277{
278 X509_OBJECT *ret = X509_OBJECT_new();
279
280 if (ret == NULL)
281 return NULL;
282 if (!X509_STORE_CTX_get_by_subject(vs, type, name, ret)) {
283 X509_OBJECT_free(ret);
284 return NULL;
285 }
286 return ret;
287}
288
289int X509_STORE_CTX_get_by_subject(X509_STORE_CTX *vs, X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
290 X509_NAME *name, X509_OBJECT *ret)
291{
292 X509_STORE *ctx = vs->ctx;
293 X509_LOOKUP *lu;
294 X509_OBJECT stmp, *tmp;
295 int i, j;
296
297 if (ctx == NULL)
298 return 0;
299
300 stmp.type = X509_LU_NONE;
301 stmp.data.ptr = NULL;
302
303 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->lock);
304 tmp = X509_OBJECT_retrieve_by_subject(ctx->objs, type, name);
305 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->lock);
306
307 if (tmp == NULL || type == X509_LU_CRL) {
308 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_LOOKUP_num(ctx->get_cert_methods); i++) {
309 lu = sk_X509_LOOKUP_value(ctx->get_cert_methods, i);
310 j = X509_LOOKUP_by_subject(lu, type, name, &stmp);
311 if (j) {
312 tmp = &stmp;
313 break;
314 }
315 }
316 if (tmp == NULL)
317 return 0;
318 }
319
320 ret->type = tmp->type;
321 ret->data.ptr = tmp->data.ptr;
322
323 X509_OBJECT_up_ref_count(ret);
324
325 return 1;
326}
327
328static int x509_store_add(X509_STORE *ctx, void *x, int crl) {
329 X509_OBJECT *obj;
330 int ret = 0, added = 0;
331
332 if (x == NULL)
333 return 0;
334 obj = X509_OBJECT_new();
335 if (obj == NULL)
336 return 0;
337
338 if (crl) {
339 obj->type = X509_LU_CRL;
340 obj->data.crl = (X509_CRL *)x;
341 } else {
342 obj->type = X509_LU_X509;
343 obj->data.x509 = (X509 *)x;
344 }
345 X509_OBJECT_up_ref_count(obj);
346
347 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->lock);
348
349 if (X509_OBJECT_retrieve_match(ctx->objs, obj)) {
350 ret = 1;
351 } else {
352 added = sk_X509_OBJECT_push(ctx->objs, obj);
353 ret = added != 0;
354 }
355
356 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->lock);
357
358 if (added == 0) /* obj not pushed */
359 X509_OBJECT_free(obj);
360
361 return ret;
362}
363
364int X509_STORE_add_cert(X509_STORE *ctx, X509 *x)
365{
366 if (!x509_store_add(ctx, x, 0)) {
367 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_ADD_CERT, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
368 return 0;
369 }
370 return 1;
371}

373int X509_STORE_add_crl(X509_STORE *ctx, X509_CRL *x)
374{
375 if (!x509_store_add(ctx, x, 1)) {
376 X509err(X509_F_X509_STORE_ADD_CRL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
377 return 0;
378 }
379 return 1;
380}

382int X509_OBJECT_up_ref_count(X509_OBJECT *a)
383{
384 switch (a->type) {
385 case X509_LU_NONE:
386 break;
387 case X509_LU_X509:
388 return X509_up_ref(a->data.x509);
389 case X509_LU_CRL:
390 return X509_CRL_up_ref(a->data.crl);
391 }
392 return 1;
393}

426static void x509_object_free_internal(X509_OBJECT *a)
427{
428 if (a == NULL)
429 return;
430 switch (a->type) {
431 case X509_LU_NONE:
432 break;
433 case X509_LU_X509:
434 X509_free(a->data.x509);
435 break;
436 case X509_LU_CRL:
437 X509_CRL_free(a->data.crl);
438 break;
439 }
440}

442int X509_OBJECT_set1_X509(X509_OBJECT *a, X509 *obj)
443{
444 if (a == NULL || !X509_up_ref(obj))
445 return 0;
446
447 x509_object_free_internal(a);
448 a->type = X509_LU_X509;
449 a->data.x509 = obj;
450 return 1;
451}

458 x509_object_free_internal(a);
459 a->type = X509_LU_CRL;
460 a->data.crl = obj;
461 return 1;
462}

470static int x509_object_idx_cnt(STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT) *h, X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
471 X509_NAME *name, int *pnmatch)
472{
473 X509_OBJECT stmp;
474 X509 x509_s;
475 X509_CRL crl_s;
476 int idx;
477
478 stmp.type = type;
479 switch (type) {
480 case X509_LU_X509:
481 stmp.data.x509 = &x509_s;
482 x509_s.cert_info.subject = name;
483 break;
484 case X509_LU_CRL:
485 stmp.data.crl = &crl_s;
486 crl_s.crl.issuer = name;
487 break;
488 case X509_LU_NONE:
489 /* abort(); */
490 return -1;
491 }
492
493 idx = sk_X509_OBJECT_find(h, &stmp);
494 if (idx >= 0 && pnmatch) {
495 int tidx;
496 const X509_OBJECT *tobj, *pstmp;
497 *pnmatch = 1;
498 pstmp = &stmp;
499 for (tidx = idx + 1; tidx < sk_X509_OBJECT_num(h); tidx++) {
500 tobj = sk_X509_OBJECT_value(h, tidx);
501 if (x509_object_cmp(&tobj, &pstmp))
502 break;
503 (*pnmatch)++;
504 }
505 }
506 return idx;
507}

509int X509_OBJECT_idx_by_subject(STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT) *h, X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
510 X509_NAME *name)
511{
512 return x509_object_idx_cnt(h, type, name, NULL);
513}

515X509_OBJECT *X509_OBJECT_retrieve_by_subject(STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT) *h,
516 X509_LOOKUP_TYPE type,
517 X509_NAME *name)
518{
519 int idx;
520 idx = X509_OBJECT_idx_by_subject(h, type, name);
521 if (idx == -1)
522 return NULL;
523 return sk_X509_OBJECT_value(h, idx);
524}

531STACK_OF(X509) *X509_STORE_CTX_get1_certs(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx, X509_NAME *nm)
532{
533 int i, idx, cnt;
534 STACK_OF(X509) *sk = NULL;
535 X509 *x;
536 X509_OBJECT *obj;
537
538 if (ctx->ctx == NULL)
539 return NULL;
540
541 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->ctx->lock);
542 idx = x509_object_idx_cnt(ctx->ctx->objs, X509_LU_X509, nm, &cnt);
543 if (idx < 0) {
544 /*
545 * Nothing found in cache: do lookup to possibly add new objects to
546 * cache
547 */
548 X509_OBJECT *xobj = X509_OBJECT_new();
549
550 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
551 if (xobj == NULL)
552 return NULL;
553 if (!X509_STORE_CTX_get_by_subject(ctx, X509_LU_X509, nm, xobj)) {
554 X509_OBJECT_free(xobj);
555 return NULL;
556 }
557 X509_OBJECT_free(xobj);
558 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->ctx->lock);
559 idx = x509_object_idx_cnt(ctx->ctx->objs, X509_LU_X509, nm, &cnt);
560 if (idx < 0) {
561 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
562 return NULL;
563 }
564 }
565
566 sk = sk_X509_new_null();
567 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++, idx++) {
568 obj = sk_X509_OBJECT_value(ctx->ctx->objs, idx);
569 x = obj->data.x509;
570 X509_up_ref(x);
571 if (!sk_X509_push(sk, x)) {
572 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
573 X509_free(x);
574 sk_X509_pop_free(sk, X509_free);
575 return NULL;
576 }
577 }
578 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
579 return sk;
580}
581
582STACK_OF(X509_CRL) *X509_STORE_CTX_get1_crls(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx, X509_NAME *nm)
583{
584 int i, idx, cnt;
585 STACK_OF(X509_CRL) *sk = sk_X509_CRL_new_null();
586 X509_CRL *x;
587 X509_OBJECT *obj, *xobj = X509_OBJECT_new();
588
589 /* Always do lookup to possibly add new CRLs to cache */
590 if (sk == NULL
591 || xobj == NULL
592 || ctx->ctx == NULL
593 || !X509_STORE_CTX_get_by_subject(ctx, X509_LU_CRL, nm, xobj)) {
594 X509_OBJECT_free(xobj);
595 sk_X509_CRL_free(sk);
596 return NULL;
597 }
598 X509_OBJECT_free(xobj);
599 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->ctx->lock);
600 idx = x509_object_idx_cnt(ctx->ctx->objs, X509_LU_CRL, nm, &cnt);
601 if (idx < 0) {
602 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
603 sk_X509_CRL_free(sk);
604 return NULL;
605 }
606
607 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++, idx++) {
608 obj = sk_X509_OBJECT_value(ctx->ctx->objs, idx);
609 x = obj->data.crl;
610 X509_CRL_up_ref(x);
611 if (!sk_X509_CRL_push(sk, x)) {
612 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
613 X509_CRL_free(x);
614 sk_X509_CRL_pop_free(sk, X509_CRL_free);
615 return NULL;
616 }
617 }
618 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
619 return sk;
620}
621
622X509_OBJECT *X509_OBJECT_retrieve_match(STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT) *h,
623 X509_OBJECT *x)
624{
625 int idx, i, num;
626 X509_OBJECT *obj;
627
628 idx = sk_X509_OBJECT_find(h, x);
629 if (idx < 0)
630 return NULL;
631 if ((x->type != X509_LU_X509) && (x->type != X509_LU_CRL))
632 return sk_X509_OBJECT_value(h, idx);
633 for (i = idx, num = sk_X509_OBJECT_num(h); i < num; i++) {
634 obj = sk_X509_OBJECT_value(h, i);
635 if (x509_object_cmp((const X509_OBJECT **)&obj,
636 (const X509_OBJECT **)&x))
637 return NULL;
638 if (x->type == X509_LU_X509) {
639 if (!X509_cmp(obj->data.x509, x->data.x509))
640 return obj;
641 } else if (x->type == X509_LU_CRL) {
642 if (!X509_CRL_match(obj->data.crl, x->data.crl))
643 return obj;
644 } else
645 return obj;
646 }
647 return NULL;
648}
649
650/*-
651 * Try to get issuer certificate from store. Due to limitations
652 * of the API this can only retrieve a single certificate matching
653 * a given subject name. However it will fill the cache with all
654 * matching certificates, so we can examine the cache for all
655 * matches.
656 *
657 * Return values are:
658 * 1 lookup successful.
659 * 0 certificate not found.
660 * -1 some other error.
661 */
662int X509_STORE_CTX_get1_issuer(X509 **issuer, X509_STORE_CTX *ctx, X509 *x)
663{
664 X509_NAME *xn;
665 X509_OBJECT *obj = X509_OBJECT_new(), *pobj = NULL;
666 int i, ok, idx, ret;
667
668 if (obj == NULL)
669 return -1;
670 *issuer = NULL;
671 xn = X509_get_issuer_name(x);
672 ok = X509_STORE_CTX_get_by_subject(ctx, X509_LU_X509, xn, obj);
673 if (ok != 1) {
674 X509_OBJECT_free(obj);
675 return 0;
676 }
677 /* If certificate matches all OK */
678 if (ctx->check_issued(ctx, x, obj->data.x509)) {
679 if (x509_check_cert_time(ctx, obj->data.x509, -1)) {
680 *issuer = obj->data.x509;
681 X509_up_ref(*issuer);
682 X509_OBJECT_free(obj);
683 return 1;
684 }
685 }
686 X509_OBJECT_free(obj);
687
688 if (ctx->ctx == NULL)
689 return 0;
690
691 /* Else find index of first cert accepted by 'check_issued' */
692 ret = 0;
693 CRYPTO_THREAD_write_lock(ctx->ctx->lock);
694 idx = X509_OBJECT_idx_by_subject(ctx->ctx->objs, X509_LU_X509, xn);
695 if (idx != -1) { /* should be true as we've had at least one
696 * match */
697 /* Look through all matching certs for suitable issuer */
698 for (i = idx; i < sk_X509_OBJECT_num(ctx->ctx->objs); i++) {
699 pobj = sk_X509_OBJECT_value(ctx->ctx->objs, i);
700 /* See if we've run past the matches */
701 if (pobj->type != X509_LU_X509)
702 break;
703 if (X509_NAME_cmp(xn, X509_get_subject_name(pobj->data.x509)))
704 break;
705 if (ctx->check_issued(ctx, x, pobj->data.x509)) {
706 *issuer = pobj->data.x509;
707 ret = 1;
708 /*
709 * If times check, exit with match,
710 * otherwise keep looking. Leave last
711 * match in issuer so we return nearest
712 * match if no certificate time is OK.
713 */
714
715 if (x509_check_cert_time(ctx, *issuer, -1))
716 break;
717 }
718 }
719 }
720 CRYPTO_THREAD_unlock(ctx->ctx->lock);
721 if (*issuer)
722 X509_up_ref(*issuer);
723 return ret;
724}
